WHAT IS ENERGY POVERTY

Access To Electricity Is Limited for Over 1.2 Billion People

This forces households to rely on dangerous and expensive energy sources that dramatically impact every day life:

×
Families spend disproportionately large amounts of time and income collecting wood and paying for kerosene.
×
A transformative tool for economic development and communication, mobile phones are hindered by being unable to charge at home.
×
With limited resources for illumination, hours for family, study, and work are cut short when the sun goes down.
×
Open fire cooking causes over 4 million deaths per year. Conditions like heart disease and COPD are directly linked to the toxic smoke inhaled by the billions of people still cooking over biomass fires.
×
Open fires also release significant amounts of CO2 and produce a staggering 25% of global black carbon emissions. This is more than all the world’s cars and trucks combined.
